Description: Fragment of round hanle to moderate tuirn of Rhodian pottery transport amphora. Rectangular stamp with additonal symbol. Clay fine pink-buff.
Curator's comments: Name Damokrates. Petrie Diary 1884-5 (EES Archive XVII 47) has several stamps of Damokrates; while this one is not clearly included, the trimming points clearly to Naukratis as provenance.
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (JB.0773)
